description:
**Parent:** wiresmith-36b (gRPC umbrella).
**Depends on:** GRPC-1 (descriptor parsing).

**What:** Emit, per service:
```go
type FooClient interface {
    Bar(ctx context.Context, in *BarRequest, opts ...grpc.CallOption) (*BarResponse, error)
    // streaming methods omitted here — see GRPC-4
}
func NewFooClient(cc grpc.ClientConnInterface) FooClient { ... }
type fooClient struct{ cc grpc.ClientConnInterface }
func (c *fooClient) Bar(ctx, in, opts...) (*BarResponse, error) { /* cc.Invoke */ }
```

Match `protoc-gen-go-grpc`'s emitted shape so consumers can swap codegens without changing call sites. The runtime call is `cc.Invoke(ctx, "/pkg.Service/Method", in, out, opts...)`; serialization goes through wiresmith's existing Marshal/Unmarshal.

**Key requirements:**
- Client-only emission in this bead (server in GRPC-3, streaming in GRPC-4).
- Method path: `/<protoPackage>.<ServiceName>/<MethodName>` exactly (gRPC wire contract).
- Import `google.golang.org/grpc` (and `context`) only when a file declares services — keep empty-service files lean.

**Validation:** Integration test under `test/peer/grpc_client_test.go`: spin up an in-process `grpc.NewServer` with a manual handler, call via wiresmith-generated client, assert round-trip. Use `proto/basic/service.proto` from GRPC-1.
